{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id0db464b1-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1720"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1720"},"text":"§ 1720.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For the purposes of this subchapter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0db464b2-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1720/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “educational agency” means a local educational agency or a “State educational agency” as defined by section 801(k) ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002131"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002131"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0db464b3-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1720/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “local educational agency” means a local educational agency as defined by section 801(f) ","children":[{"tag":"sup","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" of the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0db464b4-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1720/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “segregation” means the operation of a school system in which students are wholly or substantially separated among the schools of an educational agency on the basis of race, color, sex, or national origin or within a school on the basis of race, color, or national origin.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0db464b5-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1720/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “desegregation” means desegregation as defined by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2000c/b"},"text":"section 2000c(b) of title 42","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0db464b6-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1720/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" An educational agency shall be deemed to transport a student if any part of the cost of such student’s transportation is paid by such agency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id0db464b7-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/380/tII/s221"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–380, title II, § 221","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/518"},"text":"88 Stat. 518","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id0db464b8-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id0db464b9-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id0db464ba-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 801 of the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965, referred to in subsecs. (a) and (b), is section 801, title VIII, of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/10"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–10","children":[],"tail":", which was formerly classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s881"},"text":"section 881 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Section 801 of that Act was renumbered section 1001 of title X by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/561/tVIII/s801/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–561, title VIII, § 801(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-01"},"text":"Nov. 1, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2284"},"text":"92 Stat. 2284","children":[],"tail":", and was reclassified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s3381"},"text":"section 3381 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Section 1001 was subsequently renumbered section 8001 and amended generally by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/297/tI/s1002"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–297, title I, § 1002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-04-28"},"text":"Apr. 28, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/293"},"text":"102 Stat. 293","children":[],"tail":", and, as so amended, did not contain subsections or specific definitions. Section 8001 was subsequently omitted in the general amendment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/10"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–10","children":[],"tail":" by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/382/tI/s101"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–382, title I, § 101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-20"},"text":"Oct. 20, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3519"},"text":"108 Stat. 3519","children":[],"tail":". For definitions, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s7801"},"text":"section 7801 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id0db464bb-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id0db464bc-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective on and after sixtieth day after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1974","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/380/s2/c"},"text":"section 2(c) of Pub. L. 93–380","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s1221–1"},"text":"section 1221–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
